  "lore": "For Iron Hands Legionaries who had failed their father’s rigid standards and bleak code in battle, whether tasting defeat by the fickle whims of fate or laid low by wounds too terrible to bear, there remained one course of action if their own fame or record did not afford them the licence to carry on without the scorn of their brothers: the ranks of the Medusan Immortals. Armed and armoured principally as breacher units and featuring a high level of cybernetic rebuild among them, it was their lot and their pride to fight and die with steadfast, cold fury, never breaking ranks, marching relentlessly into the jaws of hell.",
